DURATION: Long-term, with 3 months of probation period

LOCATION: Yerevan, Armenia

APPLICATION DEADLINE:  Open until filled

Job Responsibilities

– Offer comprehensive support throughout the entire lifecycle of statistical analysis and deliverables, including Dry Runs, Interim, and Final analysis activities. Specialize in oncology, medical device, and pharmacology studies, ensuring the highest quality of statistical analysis;

– Contribute to the development and delivery of TLFs (Tables, Listings, and Figures) and FADS (Analysis Datasets), enhancing the reporting process and ensuring the accurate presentation of key study results.

– Apply advanced statistical techniques, including regression analysis, mixed-effect modeling, non-linear modeling, survival analysis, and Bayesian statistics, to extract valuable insights from complex datasets.

– Provide support for post-submission publication efforts, including the development and quality control of Clinical Study Reports (CSRs), manuscripts, and other publications. Ensure the accurate and transparent reporting of study results.

– Conduct data profiling and statistical inference using traditional supervised machine learning algorithms. Leverage statistical expertise to uncover patterns and trends within the data.

– Translate theoretical statistical concepts into practical, computationally programmed codes, facilitating the application of advanced statistical modeling techniques in a coding context.

Qualifications

– University degree in Statistics, Biostatistics, Data Science, Mathematics, Computer Sciences, Economics or a related field; PhD degree is preferred;

– At least five years of experience in a relevant field;

– Experience with advanced statistical analysis and modeling approaches;

– Knowledge of pharmaceutical development process, clinical research, clinical data management, and clinical information systems is preferred;

– Strong statistical programming skills (R and/or Python);

– Strong analytical skills;

– Experience with large administrative databases such as healthcare claims survey or personnel data is preferred;

– Experience with Git, R Markdown, knitR or LaTex is preferred;

– GCP certificate is preferred;

– Excellent knowledge of English language;

– Knowledge of FDA, GDPR and ICH regulations and industry standards applicable to the design, analysis of clinical trials and regulatory submissions;

– Ability to manage and coordinate with a team of statisticians, programmers, and data scientists, delegating tasks and effectively communicating the ideas;

– Ability to explain complex statistical methods and results to non-technical stakeholders and collaborate with cross-functional teams;

– Demonstrate ability to work independently in project management and decision-making;

– Exceptional time management skills and the ability to effectively prioritize and manage multiple projects and tight deadlines;

– Proven experience in leading teams of statisticians, data analysts, or data scientists;

– Ensures accuracy in statistical modeling, data validation, and interpretation of results;

– Maintain comprehensive and organized documentation of data, statistical methodologies, and processes.

– Experience in streamlining data analysis processes to improve efficiency and quality of output.

APPLICATION PROCEDURES: Interested candidates should submit a CV to: hr@clinsoftcsd.com. Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis, and shortlisted candidates will be invited for an interview (virtual or in-person).We look forward to receiving your application!

DURATION: Long-term, with 3 months of probation period

LOCATION: Yerevan, Armenia

APPLICATION DEADLINE: Open until filled

Job Responsibilities

– Adhere to and enforce company standards, including procedural compliance, Quality Management Systems (QMS), Information Security Management Systems (ISMS), and Personal Information Management Systems (PIMS) requirements.

– Collaborate with senior management to define project objectives, scope, and deliverables in alignment with organizational goals and client expectations.

– Act as the primary Point of Contact (POC) for clients, overseeing project progress, evaluating performance, and addressing concerns.

– Conduct thorough project risk assessments and develop strategic plans to mitigate potential risks effectively.

– Ensure all activities align with industry standards and comply with regulatory requirements.

– Develop detailed project plans, including timelines, resource allocation, and risk management strategies, to guide project execution.

– Oversee the implementation of project activities, ensuring strict adherence to the established plan.

– Facilitate clear and effective communication across the project team to foster collaboration and ensure alignment.

– Review and validate project-related procedures, plans, reports, and other documentation to ensure accuracy, internal consistency, and compliance.

– Ensure all project documentation adheres to applicable regulatory requirements, industry standards, guidelines, protocols, and company procedures.

Qualifications &skills

– Bachelor’s, or Master’s degree in Data Science, Management and Analytics, Engineering (Biomedical, Chemical), Public Health, Business Administration and other programs and/or fields relevant to Pharmacology, Life Sciences, and Clinical Research;

– At least 3 years of experience in project management preferably within the Life Sciences, Clinical Research, and Biopharmaceutical industries;

– Expertise in developing and managing comprehensive project plans, including timelines, budgets, and resource allocation;

– Strong leadership abilities to effectively manage, coordinate, and motivate project teams;

– Advanced knowledge in project management frameworks, methodologies, and tools;

– Exceptional interpersonal and communication skills to collaborate effectively withstakeholders at all organizational levels;

– Strong organizational skills with the ability to handle multiple tasks and projects concurrently while maintaining attention to detail;

– Ability to create project roadmaps, timelines, and budgets;

– Risk assessment and mitigation planning;

– Resource allocation and stakeholder management.

 APPLICATION PROCEDURES: Interested candidates should submit a CV to: hr@clinsoftcsd.com. Applications will be reviewed on a rolling basis, and shortlisted candidates will be invited for an interview (virtual or in-person).We look forward to receiving your application!

BrainRocket is a global company creating end-to-end tech products for clients across Fintech, iGaming, and Marketing. ‍Young, ambitious, and unstoppable, we've already taken Cyprus, Malta, Portugal, Poland, and Serbia by storm. Our BRO team consists of 1,300 bright minds creating innovative ideas and products. We don’t follow formats. We shape them. We build what works, launch it fast, and make sure it hits.

Currently, we're looking to hire a Product Manager to join our team and make his contribution to our products.

✅ Responsibilities

✔️ Creating buy-in for the product vision both internally and with key external partners;

✔️ Deep understanding of customer experience, identify and fill product gaps and generate new ideas that grow market share, improve customer experience and drive growth;

✔️ Define the product strategy and roadmap;

✔️ Translate product strategy into detailed requirements and prototypes to the teams;

✔️ Scope and prioritise activities based on business and customer impact;

✔️ Work closely with engineering teams to deliver with quick time-to-market and optimal resources;

✔️ Drive product launches including working with executives, and other product management team members.

✅ Requirements

✔️ A minimum of 2 years experience as a Product Manager in the iGaming/Gambling industry - is a must. We will not be able to consider resumes without this experience. 

✔️ Experience in managing all aspects of a successful product throughout its lifecycle;

✔️ Technical background with understanding and/or hands-on experience in software development and web technologies;

✔️ Data analytics skills;

✔️ Market and competitive analysis;

✔️ Strong problem-solving skills;

✔️ Skilled at working effectively with cross-functional teams in a matrix organization.

✅ Nice To Have

✔️ Good understanding of online Casino operation;

✔️ Understanding of responsible gambling (MGA, SGA, DGA etc.).

Bold moves start here. Make yours. Apply today!

By submitting your application, you agree to our Privacy Policy.

Join us at Provectus tobe a part of a team that is dedicated to building cutting-edge technology solutions that have a positive impact on society. Our company specializes in AI and ML technologies, cloud services, and data engineering, and we take pride in our ability to innovate and push the boundaries of what's possible.

Join us at Provectus, if you are looking for an opportunity to make a real difference with your skills and expertise. Whether you are just starting out in your career or are an experienced professional, we welcome you to explore the possibilities of working with our team.

Let's work together to build a better future for everyone!
As a NOC engineer, you will be an entry point of communications for our customers. Also, you are the first to monitor, maintain, troubleshoot, and recover the client's infrastructure. This is a good opportunity to develop your DevOps career.

Requirements:
Experience with Linux (CentOS, Ubuntu) for at least 1 year;

Understanding of AWS Cloud;

Intermediate English level;

Analytical and logical thinking;

Ability to learn fast;

Shift work schedule (shift 12 hours, from 9 to 21 (UTC +2), night and day alternate, schedule 12h through 48h);

Experience in Network management and scripting.

Will be a plus:
IT or computer science education;

Experience with Zabbix, Grafana or any other monitoring systems;

Experience in Docker, Kubernetes, opentelemetry.

Responsibilities:
Monitor all of our data centers, servers, applications, performance and availability;

Assess and prioritize faults, and respond or escalate accordingly;

Providing 24/7 technical support;

Verbal and written communications with customers;

Follow NOC processes and procedures for efficient monitoring and communication;

Troubleshoot issues by utilizing provided toolbox and define new advanced tools.

We offer:
Attractive professional and educational opportunities, interesting technical projects, chances to engage with the latest technologies and fun colleagues who make every online and offline event a treat. Find out more about our company: https://provectus.com/.

We may use artificial intelligence (AI) tools to support parts of the hiring process, such as reviewing applications, analyzing resumes, or assessing responses. These tools assist our recruitment team but do not replace human judgment. Final hiring decisions are ultimately made by humans. If you would like more information about how your data is processed, please contact us.

SIMPLE is a successful mobile product with over 15 million unique downloads, more than 300K 5-star reviews, and over 50% year-over-year revenue growth.It offers judgment-free, gentle guidance toward balanced nutrition, a healthy relationship with food, and ultimately, improved health and well-being. Built with flexibility and convenience in mind, the app is a safe and supportive space to get actionable feedback, learn, and increase confidence. SIMPLE’s method is shaped by a global team of nutrition, behavior change, digital health, and medical experts. The journey is enhanced through Avo, a personal wellness assistant within the app that provides timely suggestions and real-time answers.With SIMPLE as a partner in their pocket, users feel cared for and empowered to embrace — and stick to — new healthy habits. To learn more, visit simple.life.Right now we are looking for a talented Product Analyst who enjoys exploring product metrics, uncovering insights, and helping drive growth through analytical thinking.This role is perfect for someone who thrives in a fast-paced environment, takes initiative in analyzing trends, and provides actionable recommendations.Push the pace of innovation and build a future of a healthier world with us!
What we’re looking for:Advanced SQL skills – ability to write complex queries using joins, window functions, CTEs, and aggregations; optimize query performance for large datasets;Experience working with ETL pipelines and building data workflows (Airflow, dbt, or similar); understanding how to ensure data quality, reliability, and timely delivery;Basic Python for data analysis and automation;Experience with any BI tool (Looker, Superset, Tableau, Power BI, or similar);Understanding of fundamental statistics, A/B tests, and experimentation concepts (proper test design, power calculation, post-hoc analysis, etc.);Ability to structure and interpret data, ensuring accuracy and meaningful insights;Strong communication skills to collaborate effectively with product, marketing, and other teams;A proactive mindset—someone who enjoys diving into data, identifying trends, and proposing opportunities for growth.Nice to have:Experience working as a product or data analyst specifically in a subscription-based service (SaaS, mobile subscriptions, OTT, etc.);Experience running pricing A/B experiments.What you'll do:Assist in evaluating experiments and interpreting results to optimize product initiatives;Participate in evaluating pricing experiments and interpreting results to inform product and marketing strategies;Work on improving the existing LTV forecasting model and develop additional predictive models as needed;Build reports and dashboards to provide visibility into product trends and opportunities;Identify and explore potential growth levers based on data-driven insights;
Perks and benefits:Competitive salary package commensurate with experience;Remote, in-office, and hybrid work opportunities;The equipment you need to do your job;A premium SIMPLE subscription;21 days annual leave, plus bank holidays (those observed where you live);Flexible hours. We focus on your results, not how long you spend at your desk.
